    "(2) When K=1, the performance of the model decreases Fig. 3 Performance with different hyperparameters significantly, with an average decrease of 2.38.",
    "This phenomenon indicates that the model cannot fully learn event semantics when the context has only one description of similar event types.",
    "Research on the Methods of Sentence EncodingIn Sect. 3.3, we use SBERT [30] as our sentence encoder.",
    "In this section, we do comparison experiments to investigate the difference in performance between SBERT and the direct method.",
    "The direct method for obtaining sentence representations is to use contextual encoder to obtain the representation of all tokens in a sentence, and then use the mean-pooled result of all token representations as mentioned in Sect. 3.3.When using SBERT, we employed the model with the parameter \"roberta-large-nli-stsbmean-tokens\"."
